ENTRY       EC 6.2.1.36                 Enzyme
NAME        3-hydroxypropionyl-CoA synthase;
            3-hydroxypropionyl-CoA synthetase (AMP-forming);
            3-hydroxypropionate---CoA ligase
CLASS       Ligases;
            Forming carbon-sulfur bonds;
            Acid-thiol ligases
SYSNAME     hydroxypropionate:CoA ligase (AMP-forming)
REACTION    3-hydroxypropionate + ATP + CoA = 3-hydroxypropionyl-CoA + AMP + diphosphate [RN:R09286]
ALL_REAC    R09286
SUBSTRATE   3-hydroxypropionate [CPD:C01013];
            ATP [CPD:C00002];
            CoA [CPD:C00010]
PRODUCT     3-hydroxypropionyl-CoA [CPD:C05668];
            AMP [CPD:C00020];
            diphosphate [CPD:C00013]
COMMENT     Catalyses a step in the 3-hydroxypropionate/4-hydroxybutyrate cycle, an autotrophic CO2 fixation pathway found in some thermoacidophilic archaea [1,2].
            The enzymes from Metallosphaera sedula and Sulfolobus tokodaii can also use propionate, acrylate, acetate, and butanoate as substrates [2], and are thus different from EC 6.2.1.17 (propionate---CoA ligase), which does not accept acetate or butanoate.
